  "function_name": "MaybeRaceCacheWithNetwork",
  "justification": "This function matches all described behaviors: (1) queries nsINetworkLinkService for the current link type; (2) returns immediately if the link type is metered/cellular (i.e., not ETHERNET, USB, WIFI, or UNKNOWN-on-non-Android); (3) returns immediately if mLoadFlags contains LOAD_ONLY_FROM_CACHE or LOAD_NO_NETWORK_IO; (4) returns immediately if mStatus indicates failure (NS_FAILED) or if CORS preflight is required but not yet done (LoadRequireCORSPreflight() && !LoadIsCorsPreflightDone()); (5) sets mRaceDelay to 0 if CachePerfStats::IsCacheSlow(), otherwise computes it as 3x the average ENTRY_OPEN time; (6) clamps mRaceDelay between rcwn_min_wait_before_racing_ms and rcwn_max_wait_before_racing_ms preferences; (7) calls TriggerNetworkWithDelay(mRaceDelay) to trigger the concurrent network request."
}

